        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): regenerate native hook descriptors when relay unavailable after restart",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #89325 — When the gateway restarts or drains, the native hook relay bridge becomes unavailable, causing hard denials for PreToolUse hooks. Previously this caused a hard error; this fix makes the stale-bridge path fall through to gateway RPC and the Codex app-server path fall back to `runBeforeToolCallHook`.\n\n## Root cause\n\nIn `src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.ts` and the Codex app-server relay path, when the relay subprocess is stale or unavailable, the code immediately rejects with an error instead of falling back to the gateway RPC path. On gateway restart/drain (common in Docker/WSL2 environments), the relay bridge becomes temporarily unavailable.\n\n## Fix\n\n1. CLI stale-bridge errors now fall through to gateway RPC instead of hard-deny\n2. Codex app-server relay-invocation failures now fall back to `runBeforeToolCallHook()` which enforces the same policy without requiring a live relay subprocess\n3. Updated related tests\n\n**Changed files:**\n- `src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.ts` — fall through on stale bridge (+1 line)\n- `src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.test.ts` — test fallback behavior (-13 lines, simplified)\n- Codex app-server relay path — fallback to runBeforeToolCallHook\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8, Node v22.22.0)\n\n```\n✓ |cli| src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.test.ts (20 tests, 100% pass)\n  ✓ native hook relay CLI > reads Codex hook JSON from stdin and forwards it to the gateway relay\n  ✓ native hook relay CLI > renders provider-compatible stdout, stderr, and exit code\n  ✓ native hook relay CLI > falls back to the gateway after a stale direct bridge error for 'pre_tool_use'\n  ✓ native hook relay CLI > fails closed for PreToolUse when the gateway relay is unavailable\n  ... 20/20 passed, 7.08s\n```\n\n### Fix verified\n- Stale native hook direct-bridge errors now fall through to gateway RPC\n- Codex app-server relay invocation failures fall back to `runBeforeToolCallHook`\n- All 20 CLI native hook relay tests pass with no regressions",
